inn1.comm: 124 kph, and Guptill is off the mark with a smart clip off the pads through midwicket to this loosener on leg stump
131 kph, rides the bounce of this length delivery going across him as he glides this away through the third man region for one
128 kph, not tempted to flirt with this just back of a length whistling outside off
132 kph, looking to strangle Guptill down the leg side as he just gets away this back of a length through fine leg
132 kph, concentrating on the same line against McCullum as he whips away this length ball off the pads to the leg side for a single
136 kph, slightly fuller now on a similar line as Guptill fails to whisk this away off the thigh pad. Looked to run a bye, but the close-in fielder on the leg side quickly put that thought to rest
131 kph, strong breeze across the ground as this one slips down the leg side of McCullum
136 kph, fuller length now, outside off, as this is defended by Brendon to the leg side
133 kph, gets solidly behind the length of this ball pitched on and around off and straightening
searching for the fuller length as this one tails in on middle, but Brendon is equal to the task
129 kph, length ball outside off and shaping away as Brendon defends to the off side

134 kph, short outside off and dispatched with by Brendon as he makes use of the short square boundaries quite brilliantly, cutting this fiercely through point. Really the wrong batsman to bowl such deliveries to...
132 kph, gets a half-volley next up which he proceeds to belt right over Bhatti's head to find the long off boundary. That is more like it from B-Mac
135 kph, finds the perfect line and length outside off as Guptill shoulders arms. Gets good carry to the keeper as well
134 kph, similar ball as before as Guptill cannot be enticed to go after it
134 kph, shifts the line a smidgen closer on off stump as Guptill makes room to just get this away through third man
137 kph, gets nicely on top of the bounce of this length delivery on middle and off
137 kph, hangs on the back foot as he flicks this leg-side delivery off his hips behind to deep fine leg
126 kph, just back of a length on a good line and length outside off as this is fended away by the batsman
137 kph, strays down the leg side as Brendon tickles this fine, hoping to beat the leg slip, but the fielder is up to the task
135 kph, flicked away off the pads through midwicket to get Brendon back on strike
136 kph, shifts his weight onto the back foot as he defends this back of a length delivery outside off
134 kph, short outside off and sits up for Brendon as he rocks back and picks his spot through cow corner to find the boundary with a pull
140 kph, the quintessential lift-the-bowler-over-his-head bludgeon to this half-volley outside off. This one sailed high and mighty over long off as Bhatti watched it go a few rows back
139 kph, fuller outside off as this one is struck in the direction of point, who is able to get his body behind the ball to dissuade the notion of a quick single
has found a good line and rhythm operating outside the off stump as Guptill leaves this one alone
134 kph, surprises him with a bouncer on middle and leg which Guptill awkwardly gets under as he initially looked to pull, before aborting the stroke
132 kph, fuller now in the same channel as Guptill brings down the bat
123 kph, fuller ball on the toes which is clipped down to mid on as they set off for a quick single
133 kph, shifts the line on middle and leg as Brendon just about manages to whip this away towards deep fine leg with a swivel-pull
136 kph, gets wisely under this steepler on leg as the over comes to a close
drifts one in just outside off as Guptill strokes this down to the fielder at long off
a touch short outside off as he cuts away towards point. Aggression vs aggression here

what happened here? Afridi is furious. Invites Brendon down the track with one floated on middle as he completely misses the line, with the keeper behind failing to pickup the take as he closed his eyes as he got the gloves behind it. Ends up bobbling out of his hands and giving the NZ captain a vital life
defended by the batsman
hangs on the back foot before locating the silly mid-on fielder right away
looks to work this one heading down the pads through fine leg, but is late on the ball
136 kph, gets nice and tall before tucking this leg-side delivery away
134 kph, continues on a leg-stump line as Guptill edges this one fine through fine leg to pickup his first boundary of the day
132 kph, length delivery outside off which is defended away by the batsman
133 kph, fires in a bouncer which Guptill evades out of harm's way
134 kph, length delivery outside off which is allowed to go across the batsman to the keeper
132 kph, length delivery which gets good carry on a leg-stump line as Guptill tucks it away close to the body on the leg side
cut away off the back foot, but straight to the man at mid-off
once again looking to get on the back foot as this time he picks the gap to find a boundary through extra-cover. Wasn't a bad ball, but the placement and timing was spot on
back-to-back boundaries now as he cuts away this floated delivery outside off which is dropped short, finding the boundary through point
looks to work this one away through the leg side now, but ends up inside-edging onto the front pad before the ball continued past the stumps

this time Afridi locates them as he gets Brendon to play an ill-advised chop on to this one drifting in from outside off, cramping him for space as he looked to glide it through backward point. Ball ends up hitting the middle peg as Brendon exits the middle under storm clouds
punched away off the back foot quite gracefully as he gets off the mark
128 kph, just back of a length outside off as this is pushed away to the off side
134 kph, into position quickly as he executes a classical front-foot defence
132 kph, straying on the pads as this is worked away to the leg side for a quick single
134 kph, makes good use of his height to fend this back of a length to the off side
134 kph, length delivery going across him as he withdraws the blade from its path
139 kph, length on middle and leg which is defended with soft hands
defends with a dead, straight bat to this one drifting in from outside off
waits on the back foot as he executes a lovely late cut to get this away through third man. Ends up running three
on the back foot as he defends this one floated in outside off
gets forward as this one leaps off the surface to clip the front pad, before bobbling up temporarily to the leg side, with the keeper making a fruitless attempt to get round to it
punched away quite solidly to the fielder on the off side
lunges forward to smother the spin of this Afridi special drifting in
127 kph, short from Bhatti as Kane rocks back to pull this to the square-leg fielder
134 kph, short again and Guptill has all day to get onto his back foot and pull this powerfully through midwicket to find the rope. Looking to get into the next gear here is Guptill
133 kph, slips one down the leg side which Guptill decides to not tackle
136 kph, gets forward to push at this length delivery towards the cover region
135 kph, onto the back foot as this is defended back towards the bowler
137 kph, straying on the pads once more as Guptill flicks him away effortlessly
133 kph, punched away off the back foot to mid-off to end the over
130 kph, fuller one on the pads which is just worked away to the leg side
128 kph, short of a length and punched away to the mid-on fielder as they get across for a quick single
129 kph, short of a length outside off which is directed away off the back foot to short mid-off
131 kph, pure timing as he defended this one through point. He is able to get this one to bounce over backward point before setting off for the run. Hit it so late as well. Looking a cut above here
132 kph, unfurls a glorious cover-drive on the up next to this length delivery which is shaping away. Just dispatched that one away with ease. Williamson looking dangerously fluent
130 kph, good use of the wrists now to tickle this length down the pads to deep fine leg
131 kph, clips this straighter ball through midwicket to rotate the strike
134 kph, short of a length outside off which doesn't quite get the carry off the deck as Guptill dead-bats this to the off side
137 kph, length outside off which is defended away by the batsman. Guptill keeps picking the fielders
141 kph, fastest delivery of the day which slips down the leg side as Guptill mistimes this to the mid-on fielder
136 kph, gets good shape into the batsman from outside off as this is defended on the front foot
139 kph, onto the back foot now as this is pulled down to deep midwicket
131 kph, length delivery on middle and straightening as this is defended on the back foot
129 kph, delivers a length ball outside off which is driven on the up through the extra-cover region
129 kph, able to glide this fuller length outside off to the gully fielder
135 kph, fuller one outside off which is pushed through to the close-in fielder on the off side
135 kph, length outside off which is steered straight to the man at cover

134 kph, has a good feel for the length Ehsan is bowling as he shimmies down the track to slam this through long off as the mid-off fielder chases in vain. Kane looking to make sure Ehsan doesn't fall into a good rhythm
136 kph, short outside off and pulled quite powerfully through midwicket, but unlucky to find the fielder once more in the deep. He really did middle this, but it has been that kind of day for Gups
141 kph, back of a length with good carry outside off as this just whistles by the outside edge. That is the length he should be looking to bowl to
141 kph, length outside off and nibbling in as Kane brings down the almighty willow
139 kph, squirts away a single square off the wicket to this back of a length which straightens on off
135 kph, length delivery outside off which is defended solidly by the batsman
138 kph, fuller one now, outside off, which is drilled straight to mid-off
lobs one up outside off as Kane cuts away through the point region
able to ease a single through mid-on
tossed up on middle and leg on a full length as Guptill employs the sweep to good effect, getting this through backward square to find the boundary. Better placement there from Gups
half-trekker outside off which is slapped away through cover, but should have gone for more runs
punched away off the back foot through long-off

succeeds in getting Guptill to go after this shorter one outside off through backward point, as he cuts away rather uppishly to offer a smidgen of a chance to the leaping fielder, but the spin imparted off the blade meant it was always going to the left and away from the fielder
130 kph, short of a length outside off which is tucked away to the mid-on fielder
134 kph, gets nicely behind the line to defend this one away to the off side
130 kph, able to run this back of a length outside off to the third man fielder
132 kph, overpitched outside off as Guptill looks to drive this just past the bowler on his left, but Ehsan sticks out his left boot to deflect it away to mid-off
136 kph, plants his front foot across before Ehsan effortlessly through the line to whip this over cow corner for four
133 kph, seeking a boundary now square off the wicket but finds the fielder at sweeper cover
tucked away off the pads to the leg side
tosses in a full one on middle which is struck back at the bowler
able to pickup a single through extra-cover to bring up the 50-run partnership
waits on the back foot before easing this away to long on
thought about attacking this shorter one through the off side before picking his spot through cow corner to blast away a boundary with a powerful pull
invited to go down the track as he looked to go after Sohail, but this one spins into his foot after pitching as he brought the blade down. Able to get back to his crease before any incident
135 kph, tries to slap this fuller length outside off through mid-on but doesn't quite get it off...
131 kph, goes across his stumps as he looks to ease this through midwicket, but is unable to
133 kph, in the zone for Guptill as he gets into position quickly to drive on the up through the covers. Free flow of the blade as he went through the stroke. Looking a lot more assured now
132 kph, initially looking to get this length away through the off side before miscuing more towards mid-on
133 kph, pushes at this length delivery outside off, but locates mid-off soon after
132 kph, gets his head over the line of this length ball to work it away to the leg side
onto the back foot as this one is worked down to the long on fielder
pushed away off the back foot as long on is called into play once more
has a go at this wider one outside off as Sohail induces the outside edge, but with no slipper behind it turns out to be a safe option
drills this one floated in outside off to the cover fielder
too wide outside off now as Guptill is able to reach out to cut this away behind square for a couple
able to pick off a single through long off to end the over
135 kph, width on offer as Guptill intentionally slashes this one through the gully region to pick up four
137 kph, able to nurdle a single off the back foot past a diving Ehsan to hand over the strike. Just two away from a much-needed half-century
132 kph, looking to run away this length delivery through third man, but sends Guptill back when he realises he struck it a bit too sweet
133 kph, straying down the pads now as Kane sees this one early before flicking it away through midwicket to get the boundary. Has been regal today in his strokeplay. Looking very dangerous
131 kph, this time shuffles over a touch to the off side to open the face and glide this down to third man
134 kph, able to ease away a single off the last ball to the man at long on

not quite got his lines right as this one slips down leg, with Guptill tickling it round the corner to bring up a most important landmark as he crosses fifty. He will want to make this a big one as NZ look to get him into form
defended off the back foot to the bowler
able to clip this one away through to deep midwicket, running the first one hard before returning in time for the second
defended on the front foot now as the ball rolls to the off side
worked away to the leg side, but can't pinch the single
half-trekker which is given the treatment, but Guptill is unlucky to once again pick the fielder in the deep, this time at midwicket
drifts one in from outside off as the batsman presses forward
fires in another one which drifts into the pads. Defended back to the bowler
gets Guptill to top-edge the sweep through backward square, but not enough for it to carry to the fielder on the circle
worked away efficiently to the leg side by Kane
able to steer this one past Afridi towards mid-off
opens the face to this one pitched outside off as this one just races away across the outfield to the third man boundary
whips away this back of a length off the pads to deep square-leg
slaps away this length delivery outside off to sweeper cover
short ball slanting down leg as Kane utilises the angle to place this in the gap between square-leg and midwicket
short again as Kane bends the back knee to pull this through cow corner, but doesn't quite get it where he wanted
waits on the back foot, looking to run this one through third man, but finds the fielder on the circle
able to lift Younis over cow corner with a clean swing of the bat to bring up his 50. That bludgeon also brings up the 100-run stand as well, that too at better than run-a-ball
lunges forward before defending away to the off side
gets to the pitch before easing away through long on
short from Afridi as Kane bends the back knee before pulling aerially through midwicket to pickup four more
this time unfurls the drive through extra-cover to get NZ past 150
on the back foot before steering this one down to long on
succeeds in getting Guptill to play at one on the pads which bobbles up off the leading edge, with the keeper coming round to try and pickup the catch, but the ball dies on him
flighted on off as Kane uses his feet straightaway to steer this straight to deep extra-cover
waits and waits before lifting Shehzad high over long off to get six runs. Wonderful strike from Guptill
looking to get this one to the right of Shehzad now, but the part-timer puts in the full-blooded dive to pick it off
able to shuffle onto the back foot and work away a couple through midwicket. Played with soft hands
able to cut this one away off the back foot, but straight to point

cut away outside off as the spin takes it away from the blade. The fielder in the deep at deep cover puts in the dive but doesn't get enough on it as a secondary fielder has to come in his place to throw the ball from the deep
driven quite solidly to the man at deep cover
punched away off the back foot now as he locates the cover fielder
gets down the track before just about getting bat on ball to pickup a single on the leg side
looks to run one down past short third man, but picks the fielder
presses forward before squirting away a single through the off side
onto the back foot now as he punches this down to the deep extra-cover fielder
lobs one up on leg which is worked with the angle as he sweeps round the corner

and it takes this full toss outside off which could have been hit anywhere, to end Guptill's stay at the crease as he ends up holing out directly to the long-off fielder, who probably couldn't believe his luck at getting one his way. Guptill was hunched over, head down as he realised his fate. Terrible way to go, but NZ will be happy he got some time out in the middle
gets across to the off side before nurdling this one past a diving Shehzad on his left to find long off
Kane gets forward before easing this one through midwicket for one
gets one away on the leg side as the pair scamper one
waits on the back foot before punching this one through to the cover fielder. Able to still pickup a single though
gets the blade down in the nick of time to this faster one pushed through outside off
reaches out to steer this Afridi special to the cover fielder
looking to steer one past the cover fielder, but is thwarted in his attempt
this time worked away to the leg side by the batsman
whipped away off the pads for a comfortable single
eased away off the back foot through mid-on to end the over
struck back at the bowler by Kane
this time picks his spot to find the man at deep extra-cover
able to get away Shehzad through mid-off now as they take a single
hovers on the back foot before whisking this one away through midwicket
advances down the track, but the ball was slipping down leg so he had to adjust his stroke at the last second to get this more through midwicket
gives up a juicy full toss which is hammered straight to deep midwicket in what seemed like an instant
tossed up outside off as Kane fails to strike this one through the covers
scythes this one outside off straight to the fielder at point
is late outside off as he looked to get low to cut this through third man
tucks away a single through midwicket as he initially looked for two, before realising how risky the proposition was with the fielder at deep midwicket closing upon it
looks to nurdle this fuller one on the pads past silly mid-on, but fails to do so
able to induce an outside edge as Ross looked to open the face, but with no one in the area, this one runs away to the third man boundary
floats one down the track as Kane takes the bait to get down before lifting this one gracefully over cover to pickup four. Balance was dead on as he executed the stroke
once again shows his nifty footwork with this clip down to long on
presents a dead, straight bat which ends up squirting away an edge through gully
tentatively defended on the front foot to the leg side
drives this one firmly to the man at deep extra-cover
short and Kane waits on it, but is unlucky to pick the deep midwicket fielder on the bounce with this pull
135 kph, starts off with a back of a length line outside off which is slapped away to deep extra-cover
136 kph, goes after this length delivery outside off, getting an edge which streaks away to the fielder at third man
136 kph, looks to glide this one past the gully fielder, but fails to do so
137 kph, initially looked to pull this short one outside off through midwicket before aborting the stroke
138 kph, length on middle and leg which is crashed away to the cover fielder
135 kph, too short from Bhatti and Kane is into position quickly to ramp this high over third man to get four runs
128 kph, short of a length which is tucked away to the leg side for a quick single. Also brings up the NZ 200
126 kph, length on off which is slammed through the line by Kane as he finds the gap at long off
121 kph, full on middle as this one is drilled straight to long on
123 kph, able to ease this one down to long on for another straightforward single

128 kph, Kane is really playing on another level as he uses his feet to get down to this length delivery before placing this over extra-cover to get the boundary. Absolutely safe as this whistled through the air to the rope
101 kph, delivers a good slower ball outside off which the batsman sees early before checking his drive to the man at mid-off
flights one in outside off as this is defended on the front foot
shimmies down before clipping this through to deep midwicket
eases one away through long on now to get off strike
tucked away towards midwicket, with some lackadaisical fielding affording the extra run which shouldn't have been there
defended safely on the front foot and with soft hands
moves to 95 now with an expertly-placed lofted cover drive which is executed to perfection. Kane didn't try to over hit that one as he found the gap with ease
slips one down leg as Ross is able to reach out to poke this one away through mid-on
gets down the track to move on to 99 with a well-placed chip through midwicket which beats the converging fielder from deep square-leg

and gets to his 100 with a drive through mid-off as the Napier crowd rises up to applaud a sterling effort with the bat. You can see a number of people hailing their allegiance to the almighty Williamson. Has really been a chanceless innings
hovers on the back foot before picking the gap through gully with a late cut
unable to pickup the single on the leg side
just about gets away this one skidded in on middle and off behind square. Very close that
126 kph, delivers a back of a length which carries off the deck as Kane goes for the ramp, but doesn't quite middle it like the one he got away earlier, as this one falls in front of third man
123 kph, is well late on this back of a length going across him as the keeper collects from behind
132 kph, defended away off the back foot to the off side
126 kph, safely negotiates this length delivery on middle and leg
123 kph, able to edge one away intentionally through the vacant slip region to find third man
132 kph, shuffles over to his off stump but fails to get this one away where he would have liked it, instead hitting it more towards the square-leg fielder
able to nurdle a single down to long off for one
gets down the track before chipping Afridi over the covers to find the boundary rope. All his shots have come off with effortless elegance
this time punched away off the back foot to deep extra-cover
gets a leading edge as he looked to tickle one down leg, with the ball landing safely on the off side
uses his feet to get close before cutting away fiercely in front of square to find the boundary in a hurry

second time now that Sarfraz has failed to complete a stumping down the leg side. And that too of Afridi. Sarfraz not happy at all after failing to get at that one which Ross played all around. Afridi doesn't even have a word or glare. Called wide in the end
defended away to the leg side as Afridi storms off from the middle
131 kph, tries to run this one behind square, but locates the fielder at point
131 kph, pulls this length delivery hard through midwicket, but finds the fielder in the deep in no time

118 kph, slower ball on length which Kane, backing away to the leg side, tries to hit through the line with the intention of getting it through long off, but doesn't quite get it as mid-off fields the ball before firing in a throw at the non-striker's, which connects but because the batsman had made his ground, they are able to run the overthrow
125 kph, classic hook shot which sails high over backward square to go a couple of rows back. Irfan not really bowling at full tilt today
138 kph, once again looks to back away but gets away too far as he bends over in an attempt to reach out to this wider one going across him

111 kph, probably the only way Kane was going to go as he looks to be adventurous as he shuffles over to middle and off before paddling this length ball straight to short backward square, who takes it comfortably. Ends a superb innings from the young right-hander. Has been in terrific form of late
drifts one in from outside off as this is struck towards the cover region
pushes hard at this tossed up delivery from the spinner, but he puts in a good dive to his left to collapse on top of the ball
rushes Elliott to nurdle one down the leg side as he gets off the mark with a single
looks to tickle this one down the leg side, but is late on it as it catches the thigh pad
gets down the track to work this down to the man at long on
lunges forward to close the gap between bat and pad to end the 40th over
136 kph, length outside off which Taylor is late on as he flashes hard at it
139 kph, solid, crunching drive on the up, but doesn't get enough on it to beat the dive from the mid-off fielder
139 kph, full again as this time the cover fielder is located on the off side
125 kph, short outside off and cut away hard by Taylor through backward point
139 kph, slanting down the pads now as Taylor works with the angle to get this down to deep fine leg
120 kph, slower ball outside off which Taylor adjusts his stroke to, but not enough to get it past the man at point
goes down before slashing through the line to find deep cover
once again looking to go down the track, with his intention to go over cover, but ends up offering an outside edge which flies to where the slips would have been
is well late on this sweep through midwicket, with the ball spinning away to the keeper
this time chips over cover to find the fielder in the deep on once bounce
nurdles a single through the leg side as the pair scamper quickly for the run
shimmies down and follows this one slanting down leg as he clips away to deep midwicket, running the first one hard to get back for the second before the throw

dropped, 136 kph, first serious blunder in the deep as Taylor goes hard after this length delivery, pulling it straight to the man at deep midwicket who has to run to his left before diving to try and catch this, but the ball went off the knee. Looked like it may have hurt him too
140 kph, fires in a useful, pacy yorker on middle which is dug out and edged away fine through the slip region
142 kph, might be a quick delivery, but if you bowl a leg-side delivery then it will be given the treatment as Elliott picks his spot behind square before hammering this hard to get to the rope
142 kph, just stand and deliver from Elliott as this time he looks to club over long off, but ends up hitting in on the bounce to mid-off, who puts in a fine stop as he went for the dive

138 kph, when Taylor starts striking the ball like this, you better watch out. Just bludgeons this length delivery going down leg over wide midwicket as it went effortlessly into the stands. Trademark thump from Rosco gets him to 43
143 kph, full, outside off as Ross is late on as he attempts to grope at the ball
129 kph, begins with a yorker on middle and off which only concedes a single as Elliott digs it out and goes for the run

127 kph, full again as Taylor this time digs it out, but straight back to the bowler. Irfan picks up the follow through and fires in a throw, but it looks like Taylor makes his ground as he averted away from the throw. Was mild interest among the Pakistanis, but the umpire remained unfazed

122 kph, length going across him which is lofted high and handsome over deep extra-cover, with the impression given that it was going to spell his demise, but in the end it falls a long way from the fieldsman chasing after it, and ends up going across the rope
132 kph, slogs Irfan again through the line, miscuing this pull to go high over square-leg, but ends up not carrying a lot further to the man in the deep
136 kph, excellent yorker on leg stump which Elliott just about manages to dig out before getting the single in the end thanks to Ross' backing up
117 kph, deceives the batsman with a slow bouncer which goes across him as the ball is edged away to the off side
goes right after this length delivery outside off as he gets another fortuitous edge away through the slips to bring up his fifty. Builds on the hard work from Williamson and Guptill before.
140 kph, gives him width outside off to free his arms and Taylor complies with a bludgeon through the line to find the short, square boundary in a hurry

146 kph, fastest ball of the day which is effectively turned into a full toss after it slips out wrong from Bhatti's hand, Taylor slogs through the line to find the midwicket boundary. Swung it like a baseball bat as that made sweet contact to find the rope
141 kph, able to get away a single through the leg side to register the 300th run for NZ
134 kph, looks to be cute by shuffling over outside oft to paddle thorugh fine leg, but ends up getting it away squarer than he would have liked

143 kph, Bhatti gets it wrong again as he lets slip another full toss, this time higher and outside off, as all Taylor has to do is swivel in his spot to club this high over midwicket into the stands. You simply can't bowl those kind of balls to Taylor in this form. Suddenly getting flashes of Pallekele 2011 v Akhtar
124 kph, short of a length and whipped away off the pads to the leg side
134 kph, goes well down the leg side now as the umpire signals to the scorer
118 kph, follows the line of this slow bouncer going across him to the keeper
131 kph, goes on the charge as he gets this fuller length delivery on leg to go up and over Irfan on the bounce as this continues down to long on
115 kph, slow ball on leg which he gets a leading edge to as the ball bobbles to the off side
134 kph, short of a length and cramping him as it rises in an awkward area as they just about scrape the run with a drop-and-go single
133 kph, searching for the yorker as this one ends up being a low full toss which is hit away to long on
112 kph, delivers a back of a length bouncer which Elliott clubs away through midwicket
134 kph, full and in this kind of form Ross will not be merciful as he drills through the covers crispy to find four runs. No one bothered to move as this blazed across the grass
135 kph, just slipping down the leg side as Taylor fails to tickle this away fine
134 kph, didn't quite get the timing right as he looked to scythe this fuller one through the covers

126 kph, Elliott, who knows quick runs are the order of the moment, gets on one knee before lifting this high over backward square, where the fielder waits in the deep to take the catch. Some respite for Pakistan, but it also signals the arrival of Luke Ronchi to the crease
130 kph, just not going Pakistan's way as Taylors picks up a boundary on the off side by opening the face to get it past the fielders in the ring
135 kph, picks up the single on the leg side to retain strike, much to the bowling attack's dismay

120 kph, Taylor continuing from where he left off as he lifts Irfan high over extra-cover to just get this over the rope. Opened the face, and used the breeze, to help get this one away where he desired
133 kph, short on leg and this time Taylor hooks fine to pickup a boundary through the vacant region

125 kph, Taylor is in another zone all together now as he is just blazing away boundaries, this time slapping this back of a length outside off high over backward point to beat the boundary rider to the rope
132 kph, length outside off which Taylor gets bat on ball to, with Irfan putting in a dive to try and stop him from taking the single, but ends up allowing the run to go ahead

136 kph, goes round the wicket to Ronchi as he has no choice but to give it the kitchen sink, which he does as it appears he may have had an edge on it as it passed through. Misbah decides to go for the review despite the initial not out call from the umpire. Doesn't appear to be any mark on the bat from HotSpot. Was a noise as the ball went past the blade though. There is some activity on Snicko too. Would be helpful to get a better angle of it though. The final decision comes through and it looks like the decision has been reverse as Luke is given his marching orders. Luke, in disbelief at the decision, finally accepts and walks off, much to the dismay of the Napier crowd who were hoping for some bonus fireworks from the wicketkeeper-batsman
132 kph, able to open the face to run this down to third man, committing all the time for two runs, which the pair make with ease after the throw comes in from the deep
134 kph, looking to continue where he left off as he slogs this length ball to deep midwicket
122 kph, good slower ball which Nathan appreciates as he gets low to defend back to the bowler

128 kph, appeal for leg before as this one strikes on the top of the front pad, but with no fielders through the slips this ends up screaming away through the third man region to the rope. They do want the review for the lbw though. Looks like he struck the batsman just outside off, with this one maybe an "umpire's call." Looks like it will be tough to be reversed though. And it looks like the original decision will stand too
113 kph, slower ball outside off which is drilled in the general vicinity of the cover fielder

134 kph, looks like he wants that century too as he slogs through the line, but hits this a bit too straight to the fielder at deep square-leg, however he didn't get enough on it for it to reach the rope. Gets him to the other end though as he moves to 88

134 kph, Bhatti makes it easier on NZ as he offers a full toss down the leg side which Nathan laps up as he works with the angle to flick this off the hips for six over backward square. Exactly the result they were looking for as they go into the final six balls of the innings

123 kph, wide outside off and Taylor launches himself after it, getting a thick outside edge which flies high over third man to get to the rope. Moves to 92 now, with eight more needed off five to get to a special landmark

huge groan across the ground as Bhatti plays to the crowd by offering another low full toss outside off which had "smack me" written all over it, but Taylor was late as he went for the tonk over cover
139 kph, bowls a lovely wide yorker which falls just inside of the mark as Taylor fails to get any willow on this
138 kph, unbelievable. Misses out yet again on this full toss, pitched outside off. Was well late on it. Just two balls to get the two blows required

141 kph, leave it to Ross to heighten the drama as he goes to 98 after finally making a connection with this wide delivery outside off, with this one sailing high over point to go a couple of rows back. Ends up being put down in the stands as the spectator gave greater priority to his lunch than the catch at hand

and Taylor has brought up the special milestone with a flash outside off which catches the outside edge as NZ finish on 369 for 5 with Taylor making the 100th ODI hundred by a New Zealand player. Special way to end a special innings from the bruiser. Also ends a very special first innings for NZ too

inn2.comm: begins the second innings with a length delivery on the pads which is tucked away behind square on the leg side
this time elects to shoulder arms to this length ball going across him
135 kph, gets good shape on an off stump line as this bends away upon pitching
136 kph, content to simply let this length ball through to the keeper

135 kph, fuller length going down middle and leg as he ends up miscuing this high over extra-cover as the blade rotated in his wrists. Ends up falling safe in that region despite being skyward for quite a while
134 kph, ends up getting away a bye off the pads behind square as he arrives late on the ball
129 kph, starts off outside off as he gets good carry of the deck
135 kph, cramping him for room as he delivers on a back of a length on middle and leg, with the batsman unable to get it away on the leg side
132 kph, good carry again off the pitch as this one slants across the batsman
134 kph, tries to punch this one through the covers but ends up finding point instead
131 kph, far too short from the bowler as Hafeez was not even in the same hemisphere
136 kph, gets solidly behind the line of this length ball going across him as he pushes it to the off side

137 kph, indecision between Hafeez and Shehzad as he almost brings about his downfall after steering one behind square on the off side before going back to his end after advancing to the other end when backward point swoops on it and fires in a throw at his end
134 kph, fuller one on middle and leg which he opens the face a touch as he directs it away to the off side
135 kph, length outside off which is defended off the back foot
134 kph, short one on middle and leg which he hooks with the angle down to deep fine leg
137 kph, outswinger bowled a touch wide of off as the umpire calls wide
135 kph, squares up Shehzad with a beauty of an outswinger on middle
136 kph, has a mere flirtation with this length delivery outside off as he follows the inside of the line

137 kph, waits on this length delivery on middle and leg before clubbing it back over the bowler's head to get this away through the straight boundary. Much-needed for Pakistan as they look to keep in level with the required rate
120 kph, gets good bounce off the deck as this one slants across the batsman before tailing in on the way to Ronchi
138 kph, doesn't quite get hold of this pull through mid-on as they end up running two
135 kph, gets just behind this length ball coming in to him
138 kph, plays down the wrong line as this one shapes in more than he expected, which ends up whistling by outside off
139 kph, goes rather uppishly at this length going across him, as he ends up hitting this towards the point fielder on the circle
138 kph, content to steer this fuller one on middle and leg through to mid on
137 kph, into position as he looks to laser this fuller one through extra-cover, but is stopped by a fine diving stop by the cover fielder
134 kph, this time looking for the clip through midwicket which he just about manages to get away
gets away with a slog down long off as he doesn't quite get the beans on it, with this one just getting over the inner ring before continuing on to the boundary. Vital boundary for Pakistan
139 kph, straighter from Southee and given the same treatment as this time Shehzad is able to lift him directly over his head to find the boundary in quick time
138 kph, was looking to go over extra-cover again before adjusting his stroke to push this away to the off side
135 kph, short and going down leg as Shehzad follows it with a hook, but doesn't get enough on it for it to reach the square-leg boundary
139 kph, full and on the feet as this one is clipped down to mid-on
135 kph, works with the angle down the leg side to get this away to deep fine leg
135 kph, able to weave out of the way of this short of a length going across him
137 kph, crashed away hard through the covers, but finds the close-in fielder
132 kph, full outside off as Shehzad opens the face a touch to slice this away through backward point, getting enough on this to beat third man to the rope
136 kph, tucks away this length delivery on the pads to end the over
134 kph, length outside off which is fended away to the off side
132 kph, short of a length outside off which is run down to the fielder at third man
135 kph, calculated hitting from Shehzad as he opens the hips to lift this over cow corner to find the boundary. Positive start from the visitors thus far
138 kph, struck sweetly on the up through the covers, but finds the fielder inside the ring
137 kph, short ball on middle and leg which Shehzad is keen to get out of the way
138 kph, played away on the up through the covers, but can't penetrate the gap
132 kph, just about gets away the clip through the leg side to get Shehzad back on strike, who has been the aggressor in the partnership so far
135 kph, opens the face to this length delivery going across as he uses the width to get this away through point, with the ball rocketing away to the boundary
138 kph, looking for a similar result, this time towards extra-cover, but is stopped dead in his tracks
137 kph, ends up getting a chop-on as he looked to go through the covers once more, with this one missing the leg stump as it went past through backward square
140 kph, runs this one outside off down to third man for a single
142 kph, cuts this one away through point to hand over the strike
whips this leg-side delivery off the pads behind square
tries to cut this one past the gully fielder, but fails to do so
advances down before pushing at this one drifting in from outside off through the covers
crouches forward before turning this one away to the leg side
pushed off the back foot, but straight to the short mid-off fielder
looking to squirt away a run on the off side before being sent back by his partner
145 kph, getting up there in the pace as Hafeez is well late on this length ball which carries a bit higher than he expected as he followed the line
143 kph, goes after this length delivery this time, spooning a chance over to the cover fielders, but getting enough on it to just get past the inner ring
140 kph, pushed off the back foot towards the covers
139 kph, tries his best to ramp this shorter one through third man as he backs away to follow the line, but fails to achieve the desired result
140 kph, this time Shehzad is able to get it away as he does well to get under this short one to ramp it over the keeper to bring up the Pakistan 50
140 kph, looks to stand his ground and club this back over Boult's head, but is late on it
was in the air for while as he looked to cut this past the slip
shimmies down the track before striking this one back at the bowler
forces him onto the back foot as he continues to bowl a tight line
this time turned away off the hips to mid-on to get off strike
gets down as this one just about spins away as he brought down the bat. Luckily nothing comes out of it for the batsman
floated a bit more on the same line as this one is eased down to long off
140 kph, continues round the wicket to the right-hander as this one is run down to third man

140 kph, Hafeez now into the action as he hooks this shorter one high over fine leg, with this one going straight up, with it looking like he would hole out in the deep before it just carried over for six. Was a top-edge from his bat
140 kph, works with the leg-side slant of the delivery to get away a single through leg
113 kph, slower ball which is struck straight to short mid-off, who gets behind the ball solidly
141 kph, pushed away off the back foot down to sweeper cover as they rotate strike
120 kph, length outside off which shapes in as this is fended away to the off side
dabbed down to the slipper, but just can't pick the gap
reaches forward before defending softly to the off side as the pair run a very quick single
tucked away off the pads through midwicket
turned away to the leg side, but finds square-leg in a hurry
this time nudged away to the leg side as they are running every single like jacked-up hares

stumping chance and Vettori delivers the first blow, or has he? Hafeez reaches outside his off stump to try and sweep this round the corner, which Ronchi, after Hafeez played down the wrong line, ends up whipping off the bails, but not before Hafeez just about manages to bring his foot back across the line, but it does look touch and go. Most likely the benefit will go to the batsman, which it does. NZ back to the drawing board
123 kph, of course after all that build-up he begins with this loosener outside off which is fended away. I promise guys, he can definitely get it up faster than this!
144 kph, that's better. Delivers a length ball outside off which is crashed away on the up through to sweeper cover
138 kph, is late on this back of a length as he ends up inside-edging onto the body
142 kph, just sat up for Hafeez as he rocks onto the back foot to pull this one outside off through the vacant gap at cow corner
146 kph, this time pulls this shorter one more squarer to find the boundary rider at deep square-leg
143 kph, drives this fuller one on the up through the covers, but finds the close-in fielder
short from Vettori as Hafeez is able to cut this late through point to beat the boundary rider to the rope behind square. Dragged down by D-Vet
turned away off the pads down to long on
defended with a nice, straight bat to the off side
tucked away off the pads down to mid-on once more
this time steered away off the back foot just in front of point
this time worked down to the man at long on to end the over
145 kph, simply opens the face to run this one outside off down to third man

145 kph, Shehzad favouring the short, square boundaries here in Napier as he slaps one away through the covers off the back foot as he didn't even bother to keep it along the ground as this raced away
145 kph, luck is shining on Shehzad as this time he lifts Milne over long off, getting enough on this to get it past the chasing fielder from the ringer
146 kph, just follows the line of this back of a length delivery which rises appreciably to the keeper
146 kph, slices this one away off the back foot through backward point
146 kph, steered away on the up through the covers to end the over
waits on it before working this one past the bowler on the leg side
tries to steer it past the bowler again as this time Nathan gets a palm on it to dissuade the single
just collapses on top of the ball as it was pushed to the right of him, with him getting in a tangle with the non-striker
this time pushed to the right of Nathan as they ease away a single through long on
drags down the length to the leg side as Hafeez is into position quickly to play a short-arm pull through cow corner to go into the stands
this time sweeps it fine round the corner with the slant of the delivery to end a good over for Pakistan
145 kph, looks like he got early into the shot as he plays the wrong line of this back of a length outside off
147 kph, hangs on the back foot before pushing at this one softly before executing the drop single on the off side to perfection
144 kph, driven firmly on the up by Hafeez as he gets this towards deep extra-cover
147 kph, far too early into the stroke as he is struck on the back of the helmet after swiveling for the hook
150 kph, first time into the 150s this series as this is pushed away to the off side
148 kph, length outside off which is directed away towards deep extra-cover. to bring up his fifty. Also gets us to drinks as well
able to fetch a run through backward point
tucked away off the pads behind square as they scramble the single. Now Hafeez joins Shehzad with a fifty of his own to match
defended away to the off side
gets down the track before striking this one back at the bowler, who puts in the dive to get a hand on it
goes down again except this time he checks his shot as he digs out this fuller one
once again looking to get it away leg-side, but can't find the open region behind square
gets far too early into the stroke as he looks for the sweep through square-leg
this time eased away off the back foot down to deep cover
driven firmly down to long off to rotate the strike
defended from the crease tentatively by Shehzad
manages to tuck away a single through midwicket to get away from the strike, and the light....
far too late on this pull as this one seemed to miss everything as it went through to Ronchi
drags one on leg as this is clubbed away to deep midwicket
eased away on the front foot to mid-on as Shehzad is given back the strike

and NZ finally make the first breakthrough after Nathan invites Shehzad to go down the track and chip him over cow corner. Shehzad went for the bait, but doesn't get enough on it as he holes out to the man on the boundary. Ends a spirited fifty from the opener who certainly set the tone early on in this chase for Pakistan
crouches forward as he defends this one away to the off side
reaches out to this one spinning away to get some bat on it as it races away to the third man boundary, but not before Williamson puts in the dive to track this one back before the rope
turned away towards the leg side to get Younis off strike
gets nicely forward as there is a close-in field for Younis, with a slip in place
parries this one away to the off side as the short mid-off makes an athletic diving stop
turned away to the leg side now as they take a single
advances down before pushing at this one past the bowler to his left
eased away off the back foot, but straight to mid-on
cut away behind square now as he gets enough to complete a brace
Hafeez happy to nurdle one down to long on
slapped away in front of point as he bissects the gap through the cover region to pickup his first boundary
this time gets it away on the back foot through to deep midwicket
manages to nudge away a single through the leg side
once again looks to get it away on the leg side, but some smart fielding from the inner-circle fielder keeps it to none
picks up a single down the leg side to end the over
132 kph, length outside off which is pushed towards the general vicinity of point
135 kph, heading down the pads as this is flicked away square on the leg side
133 kph, tries to force one away through the covers, but doesn't quite middle it so
135 kph, on the pads now as this is struck back to him on the bounce in his follow through
136 kph, steers this length delivery outside off through the covers before setting off for the quick single
137 kph, driven sweetly to the man at mid-off to end the over
content to just steer this one down to long off

Nathan seems to have the golden arm in Napier at the moment for NZ as he manages to dismiss Younis by inviting him to have a go with a tossed up delivery which he attacks straight away, but not before he found the fielder in the deep at cow corner
hangs on the back foot before whisking this away to the leg side
gets himself off strike with a dab down to long on
reaches out to meet the pitch of this as this is squirted away through the off side
once again happy to just steer this one down to the fielder at long on
136 kph, almost gets the Pakistan captain to chop one on as the French cut means this streaks away through backward square
134 kph, wonderful pull to this short of a length outside off as the ball crashed into the midwicket fence. Sheer elegance as he went through the stroke
131 kph, shows off his off-side prowess with a wonderful scythe through point which reached the deep cover fielder in a hurry
134 kph, Misbah throwing caution to the wind as he slices this one over point, with this falling short of the boundary rider at the rope
133 kph, fended away by Hafeez to the off side
135 kph, gets solidly behind the line of this length delivery to end the over
can't pinch a run on the off side as he defends away
hangs back before steering this to the square boundary
first real loose delivery from Vettori as he gets this down leg, with Hafeez working with the angle to pull this through backward square for four
hurried onto him from outside off as Hafeez just manages to get it away on the off side with an open face
shuffles onto the back foot before nudging this away to the leg side to get Hafeez back on strike
goes down the track before striking this one back at Vettori, who gets down to field the ball
136 kph, stand and deliver as Misbah disdainfully clubs Southee back over his head to find the long off boundary. Looked so casual as he struck that one back
length outside off which Misbah failed to run away through third man as he looked to edge it behind
135 kph, short of a length as Hafeez manages to get away a pull through midwicket
102 kph, slower ball on the pads which is clipped away to the leg side
134 kph, steered firmly on the front foot through extra-cover
138 kph, full toss which Southee is fortunate to get away with as Hafeez ends up hitting it away through the leg side as he was rushed into the stroke
shimmies down the track before picking his spot at deep extra-cover. Looks like the ball might win the race, but the boundary rider is able to cut it off
content to just defend this one from the safety of his crease
looks to force the issue on the off side as he squirts one away square off the wicket

dragged down by Vettori as this is nudged to mid-on, with Misbah running the first one hard as the ball slowed up at the 30-yard circle, before coming back to complete two. Smart running from these two
this time clipped off the pads through the same region, but this time they are unable to complete a brace
tentatively struck away to the off side to end the over
136 kph, full delivery outside off which is squirted away to sweeper cover
140 kph, content to use Milne's pace to run this length delivery outside off through third man
143 kph, crisply struck on the up as he hammers this length delivery back towards Milne who is able to stick a mitt out in his follow through to take most of the sting
142 kph, shifts his weight onto the back foot before opening the face to guide this to third man
142 kph, short of a length outside off which is intentionally edged away by Hafeez through third man
147 kph, nicely behind the line of this length ball which shapes in
Elliott almost strikes straight away for NZ as he gets Hafeez to sweep high over backward square, with the boundary rider able to get a hand on it before it fell over for six

it is not often you get two chances back to back and Hafeez finally has to go after not getting enough on this to fly over deep backward square, who now has to run forward to take the catch, which he does with aplomb. Hafeez exits to raucous applause, but the shot was surely not on after having taken the big risk the previous ball. Big wicket in the context of the match for NZ, but one can never rule these warriors out
Misbah able to whip Elliott through the leg side for a single to bring Afridi on strike

Afridi right into the thick of things as he doesn't bother to have a sighter, as he flicks this leg-side delivery uppishly over backward square, with Vettori, who was at short backward square, cantering behind to try and take the catch. A direct hit at the striker's end is not reviewed, but after looking at it again, it appears the batsman just about got away it, but it was a touch lax on his part to not drive in the bat from the get-go across the crease. Would have been a horrible way to go
gives himself room to this wide delivery outside off as Afridi picks up his first boundary with a slap through the covers. Game on
now sensibly gets away a clip through cow corner, with the call for two coming off for the pair
141 kph, gropes at this fuller delivery outside off as Misbah is late on it
145 kph, another dot for NZ as Misbah fails to dig this one out anywhere where they could sneak a single
146 kph, gets away a rather awkward-looking pull square off the wicket on the leg side. Brings Afridi on strike
143 kph, bowls a monster of a bouncer which flies over everyone's heads
146 kph, slices this length delivery over backward point as the pair are able to complete two before the throw from the deep
149 kph, follows the batsman as Afridi just about manages to run this through the slip region. Worked that just in front of the stumps too
144 kph, offers up a chip to Brendon at mid-off as the batsmen are unable to take the single
pushed away from the crease as Vettori fields the ball in his follow through
backs away to try and squirt this one away through third man, but is late on it as he bent his back forward to reach it
follows the batsman as he is wise to Afridi's tactics. Unable to do anything else but dig it out leg-side

Vettori wins the battle as his miserly bowling has landed the wicket all of NZ would have wanted at this point. Gets Afridi to go after a slightly wide delivery which he is unable to truly get under as Afridi slices this high over sweeper cover, with the fielder coming forward to take the catch safely
defended away from the crease just behind square
driven firmly to the long off region to end a wicketless drought for Vettori in NZ which has extended from four years back
short of a length which rises on him as he pulls this away rather awkwardly
144 kph, splays this one well wide of off as the umpires signals to the scorer
145 kph, short on middle as this is pulled away by Misbah
147 kph, short again, this time outside off, as this is run away to the third man fielder
140 kph, just about gets enough on this lofted midwicket pull to beat the chasing fielders to the cow corner boundary. Looks like the bat rolled in his wrists upon impact with the ball

148 kph, the dangerous Akmal has to go after chopping on this fuller length delivery firebolt from Milne which arrived cross-seam. Well late on this as it crashes into his middle peg as he got down on one knee with the intent to clear midwicket
150 kph, full and on the pads as this is clipped away behind square to end another successful over for NZ
defended from the crease by the batsman
gets this one away for a single down the leg side
Misbah looking to back away before getting back into his regular position to push this to the off side
tries to force the issue with a chip through midwicket, but doesn't quite middle it
able to get under this fuller one to chip it through cow corner to beat the chasing fielder to the boundary
ends his full quota of overs with a dot ball as Ronchi comes round to congratulate him
141 kph, full delivery outside off which is steered straight to gully
143 kph, slices this fuller one outside his off stump through backward point, getting this just over the fielder to his right, to find the boundary rope
145 kph, looked to get in a yorker on middle and leg as Misbah shuffles a touch to angle this away through fine leg

144 kph, Haris, trying to keep level with a mounting required rate, has no choice but to throw the kitchen sink at this back of a length delivery going across him, with this one sailing high over extra-cover before Brendon completed the take safely
146 kph, edged away off the back foot through third man to bring the new batsman on strike
145 kph, gets through for a quick single after opening the face to run this behind square
slips in a length delivery which is whipped away to the leg side
tries a slower ball now which is worked round the corner with the angle to backward square
this time guided away off the back foot through long on for a brace
content to ease away a single, this time through cow corner
backs away a touch before reverting to his original position to clip this away square off the wicket on the leg side
follows him as this is flicked away to deep midwicket for one
145 kph, gets forward before tucking this one away on the leg side for a quick single
141 kph, looks to follow the batsman as this is worked away to the leg side, with an overthrow affording the extra run. Further penalty to the bowler as it looks like he over-stepped as well
135 kph, ends up with nothing from this bonus delivery as he drills this on the bounce to short cover
139 kph, slips a shorter one on middle which is evaded by Misbah at all costs
140 kph, ends up chopping on this slightly full delivery outside off through backward square
137 kph, too short from the bowler as this is left alone
141 kph, able to beat the man at short third man with a glide to his left to pickup four runs
offers a low full toss which Misbah fails to punish him for as he flicks this one straight to deep square-leg
slow full toss which is worked away towards cow corner for a brace
unable to get away this length delivery outside his off stump
shorter now on the same line as this is struck back towards the bowler
and Sarfraz has to depart Maclean Park with an ugly swipe over mid-off as this just floats harmlessly to Brendon, who is far too good to make a hash of that
full delivery angling in on off as this is driven away towards the mid-off region
139 kph, goes round the wicket to Misbah as this yorker is turned into a low full toss, but he is fortunate not to be punished by the Pakistan captain as he ends up mishitting this to the off side
116 kph, good change-up from Boult as Misbah is well early on this length delivery coming in from outside off and shaping towards him
135 kph, able to dig out this yorker on middle and off towards the cover region
137 kph, Bhatti looking for the slash through point as he ends up being late on this one coming in from round the wicket
135 kph, gets nicely on top of the ball before squirting away to the point fielder
138 kph, ends with a fifth dot in the over as this one is struck back towards the bowler
low full toss which is eased down to long on as Bhatti gets the strike
took all the pace off this short ball outside off as Bhatti barely gets this off the square as midwicket rolls up to field the ball
slips in a fuller delivery just outside off which is dug away in the direction of cover
uses the angle to steer this one through midwicket as Misbah is able to return back for the second before the throw
another slow delivery outside off which Misbah gets down on one knee for, but can't force it away through the covers
wins the battle in the end as he bludgeons Elliott high over long on. This looked like it might just fall short of the boundary, but in the end it had enough to carry over the rope
goes round the wicket to Bhatti as the batsman fails to get a touch on this short of a length delivery slanting in to him with the angle
tailing in from outside off as this is flicked away to midwicket for a couple
135 kph, short of a length and climbing as this is pulled square off the wicket on the leg side
126 kph, spears in a yorker on middle which is dug out by Misbah towards the bowler
108 kph, slower ball which he is unable to get away through midwicket as this pulls up around the mid-on region
136 kph, defends this one away to the off side with soft hands before setting off for the quick single, which they achieve with consummate ease
127 kph, and he is greeted to the bowling crease with a slog through long on which has enough on it to reach the rope
132 kph, straying down the leg side now as Bhatti is late on it

134 kph, Bhatti's occupation at the crease comes to a swift end as he ends up going early at a hook shot, with the ball catching the bottom edge of the bat to balloon a chance over to short mid-off, who completes the catch without issue
147 kph, really cranked up the pace here as he slips yet another wide down the leg side
137 kph, steps over a touch to the off side before caressing this through midwicket

136 kph, and Misbah goes out in the softest way possible to effectively end this contest once and for all. Did not get a hold of this short one at all as he is hurried into playing an ill-advised pull which just shoots up over to square-leg, who probably can't believe his luck at getting such an easy chance at removing the Pakistan captain
138 kph, looks like this was going down leg as Irfan, who is the new batsman, is struck on the pad. There is an appeal, but more hopeful than anything
134 kph, ends a very successful over for NZ with a full delivery on middle and off which is defended back to the bowler

135 kph, and it is all over in Napier as Boult picks up the final scalp by going round the wicket to Ehsan, who ends up offering an edge as he looked to belt this out of the park, with Ronchi catching the edge comfortably
